1. Moram *zaraditi* novac za svoje putovanje. (I have to *earn* money for my trip.)
2. Ona *zaradi* više novca nego njen muž. (She *earns* more money than her husband.)
3. Ako budeš dobar, možda ćeš *zaraditi* nagradu. (If you're good, you might *earn* a reward.)
4. Nisam siguran koliko mogu *zaraditi* ovog meseca. (I'm not sure how much I can *earn* this month.)
5. Njegova želja da *zaradi* što više novca, nije baš moralna. (His desire to *earn* as much money as possible is not exactly moral.)
6. Našli su način da *zarade* dodatni novac. (They found a way to *make* extra money.)
7. Njen posao joj *zaradi* dovoljno novca da sebi priušti luksuze. (Her job *earns* her enough money to afford luxuries for herself.)
8. Želimo da *zaradimo* novac, ali ne po svaku cenu. (We want to *earn* money, but not at any cost.)
9. Uspeli su da *zarade* dovoljno novca za svoju novu kuću. (They managed to *earn* enough money for their new house.)
10. Koliko ti je vremena potrebno da *zaradiš* novac za svoje putovanje? (How much time do you need to *earn* money for your trip?)